
[1]forgetful

   FORGET'FUL, a.

   1. Apt to forget; easily losing the remembrance of. A forgetful man
   should use helps to strengthen his memory.

   2. Heedless; careless; neglectful; inattentive.

   Be not forgetful to entertain strangers. Heb. 13.

   3. Causing to forget; inducing oblivion; oblivious; as forgetful
   draughts.
